trend_summary: The area remains predominantly low-rise suburbia, but between the earliest and latest scenes it shows steady infill: larger residential lots subdivided, new townhouse clusters, and expansion of warehouse/office parks along the main highway network. Road capacity increases and added interchanges accompany commercial growth while woodland pockets shrink yet some roadside greening matures.
notable_changes: Progressive conversion of forest strips into cul-de-sac housing clusters, especially in the north-central zone.
Enlargement of light-industrial and logistics blocks in the southeast, replacing former open ground.
Widening of the east-west expressway and addition of new ramps/intersections.
Growth of retail/commercial rooftops near major junctions, creating larger parking footprints.
Noticeable reduction of contiguous tree canopy, though ornamental street greenery increases within new developments.
